description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an experienced registered nurse with a special interest in long term neurological conditions to join the Community Neurology Service. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join a team of specialist nurses in Epilepsy, Huntington’s, Multiple Sclerosis, Mental health  and Parkinson’s Disease;  providing an excellent opportunity to develop your specialist nurse case management and clinical skills within a supportive environment. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team also comprises of therapists and support staff and the service is co-located with the Community Stroke Service and the Adult Speech and Language Service providing other opportunities for support and development as well as sharing of expertise.   &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will involve working as an autonomous practitioner in people’s own homes and other community settings. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be carrying out clinical assessments and treatment to support individuals with long term neurological conditions and their carers. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working in the community and end of life care is desirable but not essential. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As well as establishing your role within a diverse community based multidisciplinary team, an integral part of the role will be to continue to develop close working links with secondary care and with social care.    &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be actively involved in the continued development the service and need to demonstrate leadership and initiative as well as the ability to develop &amp; sustain good working relationships with multi-professional colleagues &amp; peers. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a full, current driving licence and have access to a car. Please see attached Job description and Person Specification, and make sure you can evidence meeting all the essential criteria for the post in your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Julia Webster, Team Manager on 0115 8834830&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates will be required to apply for a DBS check. Nottingham CityCare Partnership is a completely smoke free organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
